OL,6,FShe said the decision was based on a
OL,7,Fcommitment to promotion of the
OL,8,Flanguage and the importance of the
OL,9,Fstation reflecting all citizens.
OL,11,FRepresenting himself in the case, Mr
OL,12,FBryson contended that she unlawfully
OL,13,Fbreached the Ministerial Code by
OL,14,Ffailing to refer the issue to the
OL,15,FExecutive Committee for discussion and
OL,16,Fagreement.
OL,18,FUnder Stormont rules any controversial
OL,19,For cross-cutting decision should be
OL,20,Ftabled for consideration by the full
OL,21,Fpower-sharing cabinet.
