OL,6,FMr Bryson argued that the test was met
OL,7,Fbased on publicly expressed views by a
OL,8,Fnumber of senior unionist politicians.
OL,10,FThe high-profile campaigner provided a
OL,11,Fletter from DUP leader Gavin Robinson
OL,12,Fwhich stated his party's opinion that
OL,13,Ferecting Irish language signs at the
OL,14,Fstation is "manifestly" controversial.
OL,16,FEmma Little-Pengelly, the DUP Deputy
OL,17,FFirst Minister, has also described any
OL,18,Falternative view as "bizarre", the
OL,19,Fcourt heard.
