OL,6,F"It's clear that the Minister is not
OL,7,Ffor turning," he added.
OL,9,FGranting leave following submissions,
OL,10,FMr Justice Scoffield held that there
OL,11,Fwas sufficient merit in Mr Bryson's
OL,12,Farguments to distinguish it from other
OL,13,F"hopeless cases".
OL,15,F"There is one key point; whether this
OL,16,Fwas a decision made by the Minister
OL,17,Fwhich was controversial under the
OL,18,Fmeaning of the Northern Ireland Act
OL,19,Fand therefore ought to have been
OL,20,Freferred to the Executive for
OL,21,Fdiscussion and approval," he said.
